# Docker build-context hygiene for deploy/newsletter-cron/Dockerfile.
# The build context is the repo root; keep apps/web/content (the posts) but drop
# everything heavy, generated, or secret.

**/node_modules
.git
.github

# Generated / build output
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/coverage
**/.vercel
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# Secrets & local env — CRITICAL.
# A baked-in .env.local (NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000) would be
# auto-loaded by Bun inside the container and override the Fly [env], putting
# localhost links back into real subscriber emails. Never ship .env* in the image;
# real secrets are injected at runtime via `fly secrets set`.
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Editor / OS noise
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode
